         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">2[5]/5/63 ¶ Dear Mr Bentham. ¶  ¶ I have just before mail-close received safely and soundly the two boxes with specimina you kindly returned by the "Roxburgh Castle" Sir John Young, the Governor of Ne...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">63.05.25b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 103.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">2[5]/5/63</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Mr Bentham.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have just before mail-close received safely and soundly the two boxes with specimina you kindly returned by the "Roxburgh Castle" Sir John Young, the Governor of New South Wales, informs me also to-day by letter,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> that the Premier of his Ministry has caused the 50 £ for vol. I to be forwarded by <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">this</hi>
               </seg> mail to the Colonial Agents in London. No doubt you will be informed officially, otherwise however the sum will be available to Lovell Reeve on your authorizing him to draw it; at least I should presume so.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Has <name key="Acacia%20colletioides">Acacia colletioides</name> really <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">phyllodia</hi>
               </seg>? they are <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not jointed</hi>
               </seg> to the branchlets. Should we not consider them ramuli? If so the species would stand next A. spinescens, with which it agrees in habitual characters. I am aware that the nature of a leaf not requires it be articulated with the branchlet; but I think all other phyllodia are so. I have revised a portion of the proofs of Acacia, but nothing is ready for sending to you by this mail.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Should you receive any plants from Mr W. Hill of Brisbane collected in the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">northern</hi>
               </seg> parts of Queensland I should feel so much obliged if you will lay aside their examination, until the respective orders, to which they belong are coming before you for elucidation. I venture to make this request as I have Mr Dallachy in North-Queensland collecting purposely and shall probably receive from him many of the same plants, which Hill may be gathering.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have admired much the illustrations of the Wewitschia<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Welwitschia</seg>?</p>
               </note> mirabilis</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Most regardfully,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I have sent the Gastrolobia &amp; <name key="Jacksonia">Jacksonia</name>e pr "Great Britain," also 2 supplemental fascicles of <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If you are passing <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name> for the Genera<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> through the press, could you kindly send me a proof sheet, so that I may quote the pages.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the box pr Great Britain [5] small parcels of seeds were enclosed for Mr Edw Wilson</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Acacia%20colletioides">Acacia colletioides</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">Acacia <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>spinescens</p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Gastrolobium">Gastrolobium</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Jacksonia">Jacksonia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Wewitschia%20mirabilis">Wewitschia mirabilis</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
